Don't panic Tepples, the licenced famicom game "Portpia Renzoku Satsujin Jiken" by Enix did the same, rely on $2002 polling rather than normal NMI handling. Since the game works all trough menus (it was basically programmed to test how the japaneese audience was liking menu-based games, as a prior to Dragon Quest), the only real issue of this would be the cursor blinking less smoothly.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sun Jul 30, 2006 1:45 pm</p><hr />
