Склад Номер 18 (Warehouse No. 18 (Russian) [p1][!].nes in GoodNES 2.01), and Who's Cuter ( <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/cuter.zip">http://nesdev.com/cuter.zip</a><!-- m --> ) expect NMI and the vblank flag to stay stable when reading $2002 around the start of vblank, unlike what blargg found out earlier ( <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=730">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=730</a><!-- m --> )<br /><br />It would be nice if someone could test either of those on their NES (no Famiclone). If blargg is correct, the games should slow down and flicker sometimes, same as on some emulators, like Nestopia. If not, the games should run fine.<br /><br />*edit* same goes for Capcom OST (PD), and Visual Player by Memblers (PD) ( <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/vp-silvr.zip">http://nesdev.com/vp-silvr.zip</a><!-- m --> ), music timing will slow down sometimes.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=115">hap</a> — Sun Jul 30, 2006 8:43 am</p><hr />
